          </div><div style="margin:0 1em 1em; color: #999999;"><small><p><span class="srp-label"><strong>Syriaca.org URI</strong></span>: <span id="syriaca-id"><a href="http://syriaca.org/person/3193">http://syriaca.org/person/3193</a></span></p></small></div></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns" class="row"><div class="col-md-8"><div class="sources"><h3>Personal Information</h3><h4>Name variant(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-listPerson">
                    <span class="tei-person">
                        <span class="tei-persName"> The Patriarch of <span class="tei-placeName">Rome</span>, Agapetus
                        </span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/794-49" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Agapetus</span> was male. <a href="/794-50" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Occupation(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Agapetus</span> was the Patriarch of <span class="tei-placeName"> Rome
                            </span> <a href="/794-51" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">Zeʿora had enmity for Agapetus. <a href="/794-52" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">Pope
                                Agapetus, who was about to blaspheme by declaring that
                                Mary should
                            not be commemorated in the church, urged the emperor to expel Zeʿora.  <a href="/794-48" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">
                            Agapetus
                            sent a message to Zeʿora 
                            at a villa near Sycae, 
                            demanding he obey Justinian. 
                            Zeʿora refused.
                            Anonymous 3645 tried to bring him back to the city but heavy winds
                            prevented him crossing the Golden Horn.  <a href="/794-57" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Agapetus
                            died suddenly on the day predicted by Zeʿora and Anonymi 3646 accused
                            him of using magic against the Pope.  <a href="/794-61" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
